query: How many times have the Washington Capitals, Toronto Maple Leafs, and Los Angeles Kings drafted a player from Sokil Kiev, and what positions and years were these players drafted?
summary: Washington Capitals have draft two players from Sokil Kiev: D Mikhail Tatarinov in 1984 (11th round, 225th overall pick) and RW Dmitri Khristich in 1988 (6th round, 120th overall pick). Toronto Maple Leafs have also draft two Sokil Kiev players: D Alexander Godynyuk in 1990 (6th round, 115th overall pick) and C Alexander Kuzminsky in 1991 (6th round, 120th overall pick). Los Angeles Kings have draft two players too: D Alexei Zhitnik in 1991 (4th round, 81st overall pick) and RW Ivan Vologjaninov in 1992 (11th round, 254th overall pick).

query: Which reservoirs, according to the listed data, are the top three in terms of capacity and who are their respective owners?

table.title: Progressive Unionist Party - Northern Ireland Assembly

query: What changes were observed in the Progressive Unionist Party's seats and vote share in the Northern Ireland Assembly elections from 1998 to 2017?
summary: From 1998 to 2017, the Progressive Unionist Party experience drop in the number of seats won and their vote share in the Northern Ireland Assembly election. In 1998, they get the most seats, winning 2 out of 108 seats with vote share of 2.6%. However, by 2011 election, they lose all their seats and their vote share drop to only 0.2%. Even with little increase in vote share to 0.9% in 2016 and 0.7% in 2017, the Progressive Unionist Party still have no seats in the Assembly in this time period.
